snippet: Wall Street shares ended about 1 percent higher following the market’s worst daily session since November.
abstract: Stock market bounces back from the previous day's sell-off as strong earnings reports continue to power gains and concerns about Europe's debt crisis subside.
lead_paragraph: Wall Street shares ended about 1 percent higher following the market’s worst daily session since November.

headline.main: Market Rebounds on Stream of Strong Earnings Reports
